message.content:
This error typically occurs when the system doesn't have sufficient permissions to execute the ssh command with your specified private key (UserKey.pem)).

Here are a couple of things you could try:
1. Check the file permission for your private key ("~/UserKey.pem"). Ensure that it allows execution by the owner or another user who has logged in via SSH. If not, update the permissions to allow execution.
2. If your private key requires passphrase (like `-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\nY9dG6iN...\n\n-----END DSA PRIVATE KEY-----` ) , then you need to either remove the passphrase or provide it via SSH config file or during command execution with `-o BatchMode=yes -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o ConnectTimeout=10` options.

3. If none of these solutions work, try using a different private key or reach out to your system administrator for further assistance.
